# Supabase Row Level Security (RLS) & Client Discipline

## Critical Rule: RLS Enforcement
- ALL tables created in migration files MUST explicitly enable Row Level Security (RLS). Never leave a table unprotected.
- When generating client-side queries, NEVER bypass RLS using the service_role key unless explicitly instructed for background cron jobs.

## Implementation Standard

### 1. Secure Table Migration Structure
When generating tables, always append the RLS activation and policy injection blocks:

'''sql
create table public.profiles (
  id uuid references auth.users on delete cascade primary key,
  updated_at timestamp with time zone,
  username text unique
);

-- Always enable RLS immediately
alter table public.profiles enable row level security;

-- Create secure select policy
create policy "Public profiles are viewable by everyone." on public.profiles
  for select using (true);

-- Create secure update policy
create policy "Users can update their own profiles." on public.profiles
  for update using (auth.uid() = id);
'''
